com.collabnet.tracker.common
Class Handler

java.lang.Object
  com.collabnet.tracker.common.Handler
All Implemented Interfaces:
javax.security.auth.callback.CallbackHandler
public class Handler
extends java.lang.Object
implements javax.security.auth.callback.CallbackHandler

A simple CallbackHandler to be used by clients. Typical use:

  1. Call Handler.addUserPwd(username,password);
  2. configure Axis engine to use Handler as the callback handler. See WebServiceClient.getEngineConfiguration() for example of configuration. The important piece of the configuration is specifying the same username as the username specified in the first step; another important piece is specifying Handler as the callback handler class.
  3. ... now call the webservice ...

Author:
Shawn Minto, moleary, sszego
